# Testing and Quality Rules

## Backend tests

Use the right level of test for the change:

- Unit tests for pure business logic (calculations, date cycle rules)
- Slice tests when wiring matters (`@WebMvcTest`, `@DataJpaTest`) — add when justified
- Integration tests for critical flows — prefer when touching migrations/Flyway + JPA behavior end-to-end

### Commands (this repo)

This repo currently uses Maven directly (no `mvnw` checked in):

- `mvn test` (from `backend/`)

## Mobile tests / analysis

- `flutter analyze`
- `flutter test`

Add widget/unit tests when:

- Parsing/formatting logic changes
- Navigation/auth gating changes
- API client header behavior changes

## Definition of done

A change is “done” when:

- It compiles
- Targeted flows work manually
- Reasonable tests exist/updated for risky logic
- No obvious secret leakage introduced
- API contract remains consistent (or explicitly versioned/migrated)
